==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Substratum
<hw>Sub*stra"tum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Substrata</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>substratus</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>substernere</ets> to strew under; <ets>sub</ets> under +
<ets>sternere</ets> to strew. See <er>Stratum</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>That which is laid or spread under; that which underlies something,
as a layer of earth lying under another; specifically
<fld>(Agric.)</fld>, the subsoil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>The permanent subject of
qualities or cause of phenomena; substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Substruct</ent>⟦br⟧
